  "text": "For an almost incompressible material (ν = 0.4999), Gent and Lindley [CITATION_1] , Eqs. (10) and (12) offer the best accuracy for the actual Young's modulus, which was an input for the finite-element model, followed by Horton et al. [CITATION_2] , Eq. (13), with its approximations Eqs. [CITATION_3] and (15).",
